spans.content: SIGA-CC2A and SIGA-MCC2A Single/Dual Input Signal Modules
are part of EDWARDS's Signature Series system. They are
intelligent analog addressable devices used for connecting, upon
command from the loop controller, supervised Class A or Class B
signal or telephone circuits to their respective power inputs.
Module power inputs may carry polarized 24 Vdc current to
operate audible and visible signal appliances, or 25 and
to operate audio evacuation speakers and firefighter’s telephones.
The SIGA-CC2A/MCC2A may be configured as a three-state or
The loop controller assigns an address to the module
automatically. No addressing switches are used. A custom
address can be assigned using a laptop computer.
Diagnostic LEDs provide visible indication of the status of the
module when the cover plate is removed:
The CC2A mounts in a two-gang electrical box. The MCC2A
plugs into a UIO motherboard. Both modules provide the
The actual operation of the module is determined by the
“personality code” selected by the installer. It is downloaded
to the module from the Signature loop controller during

UIO versions allow quick installation where multiple modules
are required. The 2-gang mount version is ideal for remote
locations that require a single module.
Signature modules transmit information to the loop controller
regarding their circuit locations with respect to other Signature
Programmable addresses are downloaded from the loop
controller or a laptop PC; there are no switches or dials to set.

spans.content: SIGA-MCC2A: mount the UIO motherboard inside a suitable
EDWARDS enclosure with screws and washers provided. Plug
the SIGA-MCC2A into any available position on the motherboard
and secure the module to the motherboard with the captive
screws. Wiring connections are made to the terminals on the
motherboard (see wiring diagram). UIO motherboard terminals
SIGA-CC2A: mount to North American 2-1/2 inch
square boxes with two-gang covers and SIGA-MP mounting
plates. The terminals are suited for
Electronic Addressing - The loop controller electronically
addresses each module saving valuable time during system
commissioning.  Setting complicated switches or dials is not
required. Each module has its own unique serial number stored
in its on-board memory. The loop controller identifies each device
on the loop and assigns a “soft” address to each serial number. If
desired, the modules can be addressed using a laptop computer.
These modules do not provide supervision of the riser. The f
ire alarm panel must provide this function.
These modules do not support conventional 2-wire smoke
These modules will not operate without electrical power.  As fires
frequently cause power interruption, we suggest you discuss
further safeguards with your fire protection specialist.
EDWARDS recommends that this module be installed according
to latest recognized edition of national and local fire alarm codes.
These modules are part of EDWARDS's Signature Series intelligent
processing and control platform. They are compatible with EST4,
EST3, EST3X and iO Series control panels.
The module’s automatic self-diagnosis identifies when it is
defective and causes a trouble message. The user-friendly
maintenance program shows the current state of each module
and other pertinent messages. Single modules may be turned off
Scheduled maintenance (Regular or Selected) for proper system
operation should be planned to meet the requirements of the
Authority Having Jurisdiction (AHJ). Refer to current NFPA 72 and
